\title{Standards Alignment}
\taxon{reference}
\author{monaduck1069}
\date{2026-04-03}
\tag{standards}

\p{External standards that BCI Factory references or aligns with. Not compliance claims — alignment documentation.}

\subtree{\title{IEEE P2731}
\p{IEEE Standard for Brain-Computer Interface Terminology and Functional Model (working group est. 2019). BCI Factory uses terminology consistent with this standard where applicable. We do not claim IEEE certification.}}

\subtree{\title{ISO/IEC 8663:2025}
\p{BCI Vocabulary and Definitions. Referenced for consistent use of terms like "electrode," "channel," "impedance," "artifact."}}

\subtree{\title{ADS1299 Datasheet (Texas Instruments)}
\p{The OpenBCI Cyton uses the ADS1299 analog front-end. Key specifications: 24-bit resolution, 250 SPS default sample rate, input bias current < 200 pA, common-mode rejection ratio > 110 dB. These are manufacturer specifications, not BCI Factory measurements.}}

\subtree{\title{Ten20 Conductive Paste}
\p{FDA-listed medical device accessory (510(k) K990498). Biocompatible, non-irritating for skin contact. Used at BCI Factory for electrode interface improvement. Participants may use dry electrodes (Ultracortex spikes) as an alternative.}}

\subtree{\title{ITRUSST Guidelines (if LIFU is deployed)}
\p{International Consortium for Transcranial Ultrasonic Stimulation Safety and Standards. Required reference if BCI Factory explores LIFU neuromodulation. Not currently deployed — listed as a future constraint.}
\p{Key parameters: MI < 1.9, TI < 6.0, spatial-peak temporal-average intensity (ISPTA) within FDA diagnostic limits.}}

\subtree{\title{Data Handling}
\p{BCI Factory's self-serve protocol (bcf-0030) retains no identifiable data. Spectral summaries use random session IDs with 24-hour TTL. The kiosk has no internet access. This aligns with privacy-by-design principles but is not a claim of HIPAA, GDPR, or CCPA compliance — those frameworks do not apply to non-medical, non-commercial, anonymized wellness exploration.}}
